  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Networking on the impact of cross-border mining</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The purpose of this project is to establish national and international alliances aimed to effective advocacy actions in the context of the effects of cross-border mining, particularly the impact of the Cerro Blanco mining project. The actions foreseen in the project will be promoted by organisational expressions with a presence in the region, of which Caritas El Salvador is part, the Mesoamerican Ecological Ecclesial Network (REMAM) and the Central American Network for the Defence of Transboundary Waters (RedCAT).  

Caritas El Salvador has prioritised the care of the common home in its institutional strategy for the coming years, especially advocacy around the human rights to water and adequate food, working closely with migrants, refugees and displaced people. The accompaniment of the national Caritas office to the social pastoral work of the dioceses is fundamental, with a strong focus on training and local empowerment.</narrative>
  </description>
